body:
Hi,
when this code:
```verilog
module m();
reg c;
reg q [$];
reg x;
always @(posedge c) x <= q.pop_front();
endmodule
```
is verilated with `verilator --binary --trace m.sv` it triggers an internal error.
This happens with verilator version 5.010.
Removing the `--trace` option or changing the non-blocking assignment to a blocking one seems to fix the issue.

The documentation says: `Internal Error: This error should never occur ... , submit a bug report`, so, here it is.
